category = "Control flow"
title = "If Statements"
content = "You can use [code]if[/code] statements to control whether certain lines of code get run or not. Using the [code]if[/code] keyword followed by an expression you want to check allows you to skip that code if the check returns 0, and run the code otherwise.
[code]
var my_int:int
my_int = 1
if my_int:
	print(my_int)
[/code]
This should print [code]1[/code]!

You can also use boolean expressions in your if statements:
[code]
var my_int:int
my_int = 1
if my_int != 1:
	print(my_int)
[/code]
This should skip the print line, since [code]my_int != 1[/code] returns [code]0[/code].

If statements can be followed by [url=Else][code]else[/code][/url] statements."
